*Glorious music playing…

Welcome to Gemini Photos - the fastest way for you to get rid of useless photos on your iPhone. It is now available worldwide.

Some improvements in this version:

- Gemini Photos now speaks 12 languages. (Sorry for not translating this)
- The app’s performance is at it’s peak right now
- All the bugs we were able to find have scattered away from the app

- Performance improvements - as if Gemini went to the gym
- Shoo, bugs, Shoo! (Bugs running away…)

- Gemini Photos gained some weight. So much that it fits the iPad screen now.
- We’re also seeing mass migration of bugs away from the app.
The Bug Gang leader has been vanquished. (The one that would always mess up the purchases for some users)

*sweeping sound
That’s a fresh Gemini update tidying up your entire Photos library.

Our new Other feature lets you to easily sort not only similars and clutter, but also the rest of your photos. Just swipe up to keep a pic, and down to delete it.
We improved Gemini’s interface with some cool badges. Now you will know if a photo you review was edited, shot in HDR or is a Live Photo.

version_name: 1.2.1:- fix crash when scanning videos                                                                                                                                                                                Released Jul 31

version_description:
Improved stability by fixing a few annoying crashes.
Also, we apologize for not being clear in the previous release notes. The landscape mode is supported only in the detailed view when you tap on the photo to take a better look.

Gemini Photos now supports videos!
It sorts them by size, so you can deal with the longest ones first. Just swipe up to keep a video, and down to delete it. And If you want to keep just a few seconds out of the whole video, you can trim it right inside the app.

Gemini Photos now supports videos!
It sorts them by size, so you can deal with the longest ones first. Just swipe up to keep a video, and down to delete it. And If you want to keep just a few seconds out of the whole video, you can trim it right inside the app.

Version 1.2.1:
- fix crash when scanning videos
Improved the stability of the video review and removal processes. Fixed minor crashes and bugs.
Exterminated a few annoying bugs. Improved stability and performance.

Now you can favorite and unfavorite photos while sorting them inside the app.
And as usual, bug-fixes and stability improvements.
Improved performance, squashed some bugs, did the dishes, fed the cats, etc.
Our cats have hunted down the evil crash, so now it’s gone for good. Squashed some bugs on the way too.
The world is beautiful outside when there is stability inside. So we worked on making Gemini Photos as stable as possible.
Our cats got certified at exterminating bugs and tracked down the pests that messed with Gemini Photos.
Improved performance, squashed some bugs, did the dishes, fed the cats, etc.

Added sorting to similar photos. Now you can review them by date or by the event, which makes it easier to review similar shots from a particular moment. And as usual, took down some bugs and made sure the app runs smoothly.
Now Gemini picks up on exact duplicates in your photo library, so you can easily remove them in a tap. And as always, this version is more stable and bug-free than the previous one.

Burning-hot updates:
- Now you can choose how you want to review videos (by size or by date) and sort them even faster;
- Face quality analyzing algorithm got an eye check and now performs far better in detecting the best photo out of a group of similars.
Some nasty bugs are now out of Gemini Photos for good.
Made some minor improvements and exterminated a couple of bugs so Gemini Photos would run better and faster.
Added a share button so you could share your old and gold memories with friends and on your social media as you review photos. Wiped out a few bugs and fixed up Gemini to perform better.
Fixed a crash that happened when you choose how to sort videos on your iPad. And sicced our pest control team on a few annoying bugs.
Squashed some pesky bugs to make the app run better.

Happy Holidays! This update is full of Christmas cheer. Ho-ho-ho!
Get to know your photo fortune for 2020 and enjoy going through holiday pics with a bug-free Gemini, as you try to get over the post-Christmas food coma. Cheers!

New year, new version of Gemini Photos. The one that'll help you stick to your New Year’s resolutions. In this update, we've added reminders you can set up to run regular cleanups and keep your photo library nice and tidy in 2020.

P.S. We also shooed away some pesky bugs and improved performance.

Another week of self-isolation, another week of polishing our app to near perfection. Cleaning is a great stress-reliever, so a photo cleanup and a cup of mint tea is a perfect recipe to keep a clear head. Stay safe, we’re with ya!

We’ve fixed a few random bugs here and there. Made sure that the exact duplicate photos only contained photos, and skipped the videos with the same preview. And also fixed the feedback form, so now you can get back to us if any issues occur.

With this version, Gemini got two kick-ass widgets you can choose from and add to your device’s home screen.

One of them shows how your storage’s doing. Are there any free GBs left? Or is it completely packed with photos and videos?

And the one is for keeping track of your photos. It shows you how many photos are there on your device, how many of them are similar, how many of them we’ve selected for review, and how much photo clutter has piled up.

Go ahead, add them, and keep your photos well-organized.

This update comes with a bit of a story. Once in a while, every app’s database scheme changes up. So when you open up an updated version of your app, it might need a minute or two to “move” things up a bit for a new scheme. The thing is, this update turned up to be a bit heavy. Like when you put all your books in one big box instead of just a few small ones.
Even though we tried to patch things up asap, Gemini may still take a few mins to load the first time. We’re very sorry about it and working to fix it.

Great news, we patched up the whole thing with data schemes and yada yada. So now Gemini loads quickly without any problems (fingers crossed).

P.S. From the Gemini Photos team members and the whole MacPaw, we wish you a Merry Christmas and a Happy New Year! And we hope that this year finally takes us places where we can take heaps of happy pics to clean up later *christmas songs play in the background*.

We’ve fixed some nearly-untraceable bugs and made Gemini even better at weeding out useless photos.

And… that was the goon news. The less good news is that we will stop supporting iOS 12 with our next release. We’re sad about it, but still, it’s kinda inevitable.
Of course, if your device runs on iOS 12, Gemini Photos won’t suddenly disappear. It’ll still be there on your iPhone or iPad. But, sadly, you won't receive updates anymore. So please update your device’s system to get newer and better versions of Gemini.

This extreme cold has made bugs take cover in some parts of Gemini. But worry not, we’ve made them biscuits with tea and set them back on their way. Now we are bugs-free once again.
